182
00:15:51,880 --> 00:15:54,200
How about this one here?

183
00:15:55,680 --> 00:15:57,580
- A girl is flirting with you.
- History subject...

184
00:15:57,580 --> 00:15:58,200
You should be uncomfortable.

185
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:02,080
I’m not quite sure too.
You should ask your professor.

186
00:16:07,840 --> 00:16:08,880
I’ll help you.

187
00:16:12,480 --> 00:16:13,520
What are you reading?

188
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:17,040
I’m reading Prince Rupert’s Drop.

189
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:20,280
Prince Rupert’s Drop. What’s that?

190
00:16:21,440 --> 00:16:22,520
You really want to know?

191
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:28,840
It is one of the physical phenomena
of glass.

192
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:31,000
A molten glass.

193
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:34,960
When dropped into cold water,

194
00:16:35,280 --> 00:16:37,100
it will become the “glass’ tears”.

195
00:16:37,100 --> 00:16:38,200
Shaped like a tadpole.

196
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:41,080
It is stronger than other glasses.

197
00:16:41,080 --> 00:16:43,480
Layering it with an object of 8 tonnes
won’t even break it.

198
00:16:43,480 --> 00:16:44,900
But if it’s squeezed or pressed

199
00:16:44,900 --> 00:16:46,760
at the end of the tail by only a bit,

200
00:16:46,760 --> 00:16:48,240
it will shatter completely.

201
00:16:49,840 --> 00:16:53,280
Many things on this earth
that seems strong,

202
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:55,320
it is truly very fragile.

203
00:16:55,320 --> 00:16:58,640
Wow, I can picture what you’re saying.

204
00:16:59,760 --> 00:17:01,140
What are they talking about?

205
00:17:01,140 --> 00:17:02,680
They don’t even see us.

206
00:17:02,680 --> 00:17:03,420
Let’s go.

207
00:17:03,420 --> 00:17:03,980
That’s it.

208
00:17:07,080 --> 00:17:07,960
Success.

209
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:20,920
